{{Quote|What an incredible smell you've discovered!|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Episode 4">{{Film|IV}}</ref>}}
'''Garbage Compactor 3263827''' was a [[Garbage compactor/Legends|garbage compactor]] on the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]] where [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], and [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] were temporarily stranded after freeing Organa from [[Detention Block AA-23/Legends|Detention Block AA-23]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]]. "3263827" was a [[hatch number]].

The [[Magnetic seal/Legends|magnetically sealed]] facility was infested by a [[Dianoga/Legends|dianoga]] creature, which was placed there to exterminate vermin. The dianoga grabbed Skywalker's legs and pulled him down under the liquid. The Rebels were soon released from the garbage compactor when [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] disabled all garbage compactors on the detention level of the Death Star, on orders by Luke Skywalker.

It was a compactor of recyclable waste. It was destroyed when the Alliance [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|attack]] on the [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] succeeded.

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Feeling_the_Squeeze.jpg|thumb|left|198px|Luke being attacked by the dianoga in the Death Star garbage masher]]
At the time of filming, 326-3827 was [[Mark Hamill]]'s real phone number, and he decided to improvise the line to sneak the number into the film so it would be forever preserved. This caused some contention between Hamill and [[Harrison Ford]] as Ford kept repeating his own phone number, which annoyed Hamill as the reference had been his idea. Finally Ford read out the number and retorted "Happy now you big baby?", causing Hamill to laugh.<ref name="The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref>

In the revised fourth draft of ''[[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|A New Hope]]'', the film's [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|novelization]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 4|''Star Wars'' (1977) 4]], this garbage compactor's number is 366117891. In the [[1981]] [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'' radio drama]], its number is 326827.

A garbage compactor similar to this appears in the multiplayer map "Death Star" in ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]''. A garbage compactor is also in the "Death Star" map in ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]''.

